'''Ederson Santana de Moraes'''  (born 17 August 1993), simply known as '''Ederson''' ({{IPA|pt-BR|ˈɛdɛʁsõ|lang}}), is a Brazilian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[Süper Lig]] club [[Fenerbahçe S.K. (football)|Fenerbahçe]] and the [[Brazil national football team|Brazil national team]].

After finishing as a runner-up in the [[Taça de Portugal]] and [[Taça da Liga]] with [[Rio Ave F.C.|Rio Ave]] in 2014, he returned to [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] in 2015. He won two [[Primeira Liga]] titles and one of each cup before signing for [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] for £35 million in 2017. He made 372 appearances for City, winning 18 major honours, including six [[Premier League]] titles, two [[FA Cup]]s, four [[EFL Cup]]s, and the [[UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] in 2023, as part of a [[Treble (association football)#Continental trebles|continental treble]]. He won the [[Premier League Golden Glove]] three consecutive times between 2020 and 2022.

Ederson made his senior debut for Brazil in 2017. He was chosen in Brazil's squad for the [[FIFA World Cup]] in [[2018 FIFA World Cup|2018]], [[2022 FIFA World Cup|2022]] and [[2026 FIFA World Cup|2026]], and the [[Copa América]] in [[2019 Copa América|2019]] and [[2021 Copa América|2021]], winning the 2019 tournament.

==Club career==
===Early career===
Born in [[Osasco]], São Paulo, Ederson started his [[association football|football]] career in 2008 at local club [[São Paulo FC]] with whom he played one season, before joining [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] in Portugal. He spent two years as a [[S.L. Benfica Juniors|junior]] before being released in 2011 and signing for [[Portuguese Second Division|Second Division]] club [[G.D. Ribeirão|Ribeirão]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-bwin/rio-ave/detalhe/ederson-contratado-porque-bateu-um-livre-a-barra|title=Ederson contratado porque bateu um livre à barra|trans-title=Ederson signed because he shot a free kick in the post|publisher=[[Record (Portuguese newspaper)|Record]]|language=pt|date=13 November 2020|accessdate=28 November 2022|archive-date=28 November 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221128180528/https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-bwin/rio-ave/detalhe/ederson-contratado-porque-bateu-um-livre-a-barra|url-status=live}}</ref>

A year later, Ederson joined [[Primeira Liga]] club [[Rio Ave F.C.|Rio Ave]], signing a contract until 2014 in summer 2012. In April 2015, following a string of good performances and a call up to the [[Brazil national under-23 football team|Brazil under-23 squad]], he signed a new contract with the club that would last until 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://rioavefc.pt/noticias/geral/ederson-renova-ate-2019/|title=Ederson renova até 2019|trans-title=Ederson renews until 2019|publisher=Rio Ave FC|language=pt|date=10 April 2015|accessdate=28 November 2022|archive-date=7 February 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230207012655/https://rioavefc.pt/noticias/geral/ederson-renova-ate-2019/|url-status=live}}</ref>

===Benfica===
[[File:Ederson Santana de Moraes - Zenit-Benf (2016).jpg|alt=|thumb|318x318px|left|Ederson playing for [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] against [[FC Zenit Saint Petersburg|Zenit]] in 2016]]
On 27 June 2015, Ederson rejoined Portuguese champions Benfica.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dn.pt/desporto/benfica/interior/conheca-os-novos-reforcos-do-benfica-4648648.html|title=Conheça os 10 novos reforços do Benfica|language=pt|trans-title=Meet the 10 new Benfica players|last=Ruela|first=João|date=27 June 2015|publisher=Diário de Notícias|access-date=28 June 2015|archive-date=22 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180722213610/https://www.dn.pt/desporto/benfica/interior/conheca-os-novos-reforcos-do-benfica-4648648.html|url-status=live}}</ref> Then, in July, he officially signed a five-year contract with the club, in a deal worth €500,000, and set a €45&nbsp;million release clause. Rio Ave would keep 50% of the upcoming keeper's economic rights. In the [[2015–16 S.L. Benfica season|2015–16 season]], Ederson started as a second choice in line for the first team, defended by compatriot and international [[Júlio César (football goalkeeper, born 1979)|Júlio César]].

Ederson first played some matches in the [[Segunda Liga]] with the [[S.L. Benfica B|reserve team]] and in the [[Taça da Liga]] with the main squad, before playing in the Primeira Liga on 5 March 2016 against [[Lisbon derby|local rivals]] [[Sporting CP]], replacing injured Júlio César. Benfica won the Lisbon derby 0–1 and took the first place of Primeira Liga. He would then be part of eleven more victories that would seal Benfica's 35th league title, their third in a row.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/news/vitoria-revels-benfica-triumph |title=Vitoria revels in Benfica triumph |date=16 May 2016 |publisher=Four Four Two |access-date=28 November 2025}}</ref> Five days later, he played the [[2016 Taça da Liga Final|Taça da Liga final]] against [[C.S. Marítimo|Marítimo]], which Benfica won 6–2. In addition, he played three matches in the [[2015–16 UEFA Champions League|Champions League campaign]], where Benfica reached the quarter-finals. In his [[2016–17 S.L. Benfica season|next season]], he and Benfica won the treble of [[2016–17 Primeira Liga|Primeira Liga]], [[2016–17 Taça de Portugal|Taça de Portugal]] and [[2016 Supertaça Cândido de Oliveira|Supertaça Cândido de Oliveira]].

===Manchester City===
[[File:Ederson Moraes (36243872090) (cropped).jpg|thumb|right|Ederson with Manchester City in 2017]]
On 1 June 2017, Benfica announced that Ederson had joined [[Premier League]] club [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] for £35&nbsp;million (€40&nbsp;million).<ref>{{cite news|date=1 June 2017|title=Ederson transferido para o Manchester City|trans-title=Ederson transferred to Manchester City|url=http://www.slbenfica.pt/30/news/info/t8JYPAn5zkKsW8hlgu_4Dg|language=pt|website=S.L. Benfica|access-date=1 June 2017|archive-date=1 June 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170601133422/http://www.slbenfica.pt/30/news/info/t8JYPAn5zkKsW8hlgu_4Dg|url-status=dead}}</ref> At the time, the transfer made him the [[Goalkeeper (association football)#Highest fees|second most expensive goalkeeper of all-time]] – currently fifth highest –<ref>{{cite news|date=8 June 2017|title=Ederson Moraes:Manchester City sign goalkeeper from Benfica for £35 million|trans-title=Most expensive goalkeeper in history in sterling, not euro|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/40080163|website=BBC Sport|access-date=8 June 2017|archive-date=24 April 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210424093923/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/40080163|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|date=1 June 2017|title=Segundo guardião mais caro da história|trans-title=Second most expensive goalkeeper in history|url=http://www.slbenfica.pt/30/news/info/2Kdv5qwR8EychtYuojW0Jw|archive-url=https://archive.today/20170601201449/http://www.slbenfica.pt/30/news/info/2Kdv5qwR8EychtYuojW0Jw|url-status=dead|archive-date=1 June 2017|language=pt|website=S.L. Benfica|access-date=1 June 2017}}</ref> after [[Gianluigi Buffon]] (£33&nbsp;million), whose transfer fee, although the second highest ever in pounds sterling, still remained the highest of all time in euros (€52&nbsp;million in 2001) until [[Alisson Becker]]'s (€75&nbsp;million in 2018) and now [[Kepa Arrizabalaga]]'s (€80&nbsp;million in 2018).<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/44890499|title=Alisson: Liverpool make Brazilian world's most expensive keeper|date=19 July 2018|website=BBC Sport|access-date=19 July 2018|archive-date=18 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190418060217/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/44890499|url-status=live}}</ref> Ederson's transfer equalled [[Axel Witsel]]'s as the largest fee a club has ever paid for a Benfica player at the time.<ref>{{cite news|date=1 June 2017|title=Fotos: Ederson iguala Witsel como a transferência mais cara do Benfica|trans-title=Photos: Ederson equals Witsel as Benfica's highest transfer|url=https://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/primeira_liga/artigo/2017/06/01/ederson-iguala-witsel-na-transferencia-mais-cara-do-benfica|language=pt|website=Sapo Desporto|access-date=1 June 2017|archive-date=5 July 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170705033148/http://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/primeira_liga/artigo/2017/06/01/ederson-iguala-witsel-na-transferencia-mais-cara-do-benfica|url-status=live}}</ref>

Ederson was immediately inserted as [[Pep Guardiola]]'s first choice goalkeeper, supplanting [[Claudio Bravo]]. He made his competitive debut for the club on 12 August 2017 in a 0–2 away win at [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]], where he kept a clean sheet.<ref>{{cite news|date=12 August 2017|title=Brighton & Hove Albion 0–2 Manchester City|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/40835422|website=BBC Sport|access-date=22 August 2017|archive-date=2 January 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180102062931/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/40835422|url-status=live}}</ref> On 9 September against [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]], Ederson suffered a kick to the face by [[Sadio Mané]], and was forced to leave the game after eight minutes of treatment.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.espnfc.com/manchester-city/story/3199384/manchester-city-keeper-ederson-avoids-broken-bone-but-may-miss-one-game |title=Man City keeper Ederson avoids broken bone, may miss one game |website=ESPN FC |first=Jonathan |last=Smith |date=9 September 2017 |access-date=25 September 2017 |archive-date=30 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191230051215/http://www.espnfc.com/manchester-city/story/3199384/manchester-city-keeper-ederson-avoids-broken-bone-but-may-miss-one-game |url-status=live }}</ref> Ederson received eight stitches, and Mané was sent off by referee [[Jonathan Moss (referee)|Jon Moss]] and banned for the subsequent three matches.<ref>{{cite news |title=Liverpool's appeal against length of Sadio Mané's ban rejected by FA |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2017/sep/11/liverpool-appeal-length-mane-ban-red-card |access-date=14 March 2020 |newspaper=The Guardian |agency=Press Association |date=12 September 2017 |archive-date=4 July 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240704055938/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2017/sep/11/liverpool-appeal-length-mane-ban-red-card |url-status=live }}</ref> Ederson made his next start the following week in the [[2017–18 UEFA Champions League#Group stage|Champions League]] against [[Feyenoord]], sporting a piece of protective headgear.<ref name=apology>{{cite news |title=Manchester City goalkeeper Ederson accepts apology from Liverpool's Sadio Mane |url=https://www.football.co.uk/manchester-city/manchester-city-goalkeeper-ederson-accepts-apology-from-live/9111147/ |access-date=14 March 2020 |publisher=Football.co.uk |date=24 September 2017 |archive-date=13 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231113171709/https://www.football.co.uk/manchester-city/manchester-city-goalkeeper-ederson-accepts-apology-from-live/9111147/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Ederson believed that Mané's collision was accidental, and accepted an apology from the Liverpool player.<ref name=apology/>

On 19 August 2018, Ederson became the first Manchester City goalkeeper to provide a Premier League assist, as his goal-kick was converted by [[Sergio Agüero]] for the opening goal in a 6–1 win over [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/manchester-city-6-huddersfield-1-sergio-aguero-scores-hattrick-as-terriers-are-hit-for-six-a3915101.html|title=Aguero scores hat-trick as Man City hit Huddersfield for six|newspaper=Evening Standard|access-date=20 August 2018|archive-date=10 October 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231010050304/https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/manchester-city-6-huddersfield-1-sergio-aguero-scores-hattrick-as-terriers-are-hit-for-six-a3915101.html|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.squawka.com/en/news/ederson-makes-man-city-history-with-assist-against-huddersfield/1054269|title=Ederson makes Man City history with assist against Huddersfield|website=Squawka Football News|access-date=20 August 2018|archive-date=1 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190301091649/http://www.squawka.com/en/news/ederson-makes-man-city-history-with-assist-against-huddersfield/1054269|url-status=live}}</ref> In the [[2019 EFL Cup final]], he saved from [[Jorginho (footballer, born December 1991)|Jorginho]] in a penalty shootout win over [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] after a goalless draw;<ref>{{cite news |last1=Taylor |first1=Daniel |title=Manchester City win Carabao Cup on penalties after Chelsea's Kepa chaos |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2019/feb/24/chelsea-manchester-city-carabao-cup-match-report |access-date=31 May 2024 |work=The Guardian |date=24 February 2019 |archive-date=14 September 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190914004450/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2019/feb/24/chelsea-manchester-city-carabao-cup-match-report |url-status=live }}</ref> he was again unbeaten in a 6–0 win over [[Watford F.C.|Watford]] in the [[2019 FA Cup final]] as his team won all three major domestic trophies.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Taylor |first1=Daniel |title=Manchester City win FA Cup to seal treble with 6–0 demolition of Watford |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2019/may/18/manchester-city-win-treble-watford-fa-cup-final-match-report |access-date=31 May 2024 |work=The Guardian |date=18 May 2019 |archive-date=1 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200301211541/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2019/may/18/manchester-city-win-treble-watford-fa-cup-final-match-report |url-status=live }}</ref>

Ederson was awarded the [[Premier League Golden Glove|Golden Glove]] for keeping the most clean sheets (16) in the [[2019–20 Premier League|2019–20 Premier League season]] after a 5–0 home win against [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Ederson claims Premier League Golden Glove award for most clean sheets|url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/ederson-claims-premier-league-golden-glove-award-for-most/dinamu7vmzti1m0hhoxns8wa2|website=Goal (website)|first=Sam|last=France|date=26 July 2020|access-date=26 July 2020|archive-date=26 July 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200726182906/https://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/ederson-claims-premier-league-golden-glove-award-for-most/dinamu7vmzti1m0hhoxns8wa2|url-status=live}}</ref> He retained the honour a year later with one game to spare, as Chelsea's [[Édouard Mendy]] was unable to match his tally.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Wood |first1=Liam |title=Man City goalkeeper Ederson claims 'Golden Glove' for second straight season |url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/man-city-ederson-golden-glove-20633517 |access-date=31 May 2024 |work=Manchester Evening News |date=19 May 2021 |archive-date=24 May 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210524051528/https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/man-city-ederson-golden-glove-20633517 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 1 September 2021, he signed a new contract to last until 2026.<ref>{{cite news |title=Ederson: Manchester City goalkeeper signs new contract until 2026 |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11679/12396645/ederson-manchester-city-goalkeeper-signs-new-contract-until-2026 |access-date=31 May 2024 |publisher=Sky Sports |date=1 September 2021 |archive-date=31 May 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240531130319/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11679/12396645/ederson-manchester-city-goalkeeper-signs-new-contract-until-2026 |url-status=live }}</ref> He won the Golden Glove for the third consecutive time in [[2021–22 Premier League|2021–22]], sharing his tally of 20 with compatriot [[Alisson Becker]] of [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Matchett |first1=Karl |title=Ederson and Alisson share Premier League Golden Glove award |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/premier-league-golden-glove-2022-ederson-alisson-b2084691.html |access-date=31 May 2024 |work=The Independent |date=22 May 2022 |archive-date=31 May 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240531132413/https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/premier-league-golden-glove-2022-ederson-alisson-b2084691.html |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 15 January 2024, Ederson was awarded the [[FIFA]] Best Men's Goalkeeper at the FIFA Best Awards 2023 for keeping the most clean sheets (11) in the [[2022–23 Premier League|2022–23 Premier League season]], most number of saves (22) in the [[UEFA Champions League]] and being part of the City team who won the treble in 2023.<ref>{{cite web|title=Fans in disbelief as Ederson misses out on FIFPRO Men's World XI selection despite FIFA Best Goalkeeper win|url=https://thesoccerreport.com/world-football/fans-in-disbelief-as-ederson-misses-out-on-fifpro-mens-world-xi-selection-despite-fifa-best-goalkeeper-win/|website=The Soccer Report|date=16 January 2024|access-date=17 January 2024|archive-date=17 January 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240117185741/https://thesoccerreport.com/world-football/fans-in-disbelief-as-ederson-misses-out-on-fifpro-mens-world-xi-selection-despite-fifa-best-goalkeeper-win/|url-status=live}}</ref> Four months later, he was ruled out of the last game of the Premier League season and the [[2024 FA Cup final]] after suffering a fractured eye socket in a collision with [[Cristian Romero (Argentine footballer)|Cristian Romero]] in a win over [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Ederson to miss last league game and FA Cup final with eye socket fracture |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/article/2024/may/16/ederson-manchester-city-miss-last-league-game-and-fa-cup-final-eye-socket-fracture |access-date=31 May 2024 |work=The Guardian |date=16 May 2024 |archive-date=4 July 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240704055846/https://www.theguardian.com/football/article/2024/may/16/ederson-manchester-city-miss-last-league-game-and-fa-cup-final-eye-socket-fracture |url-status=live }}</ref>

Ederson made a total of 372 appearances across all competitions during his eight-year stay at the club, winning 18 major honours, three [[Premier League Golden Glove]] awards, and keeping 122 clean sheets in 276 league appearances, a record for a City goalkeeper.<ref name="city">{{cite web |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/ederson-leaves-manchester-city-fenerbahce-transfer-63892390 |title=Ederson joins Fenerbahce to bring curtain down on glorious Etihad spell |publisher=Manchester City F.C. |date=2 September 2025 |access-date=2 September 2025}}</ref>

===Fenerbahçe===
On 2 September 2025, Ederson joined [[Süper Lig]] club [[Fenerbahçe S.K. (football)|Fenerbahçe]] on a three-year contract with option for a further year.<ref name="city" /><ref>{{Cite web |title=Ailemize hoş geldin Ederson |url=https://fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2025/9/ailemize-hos-geldin-ederson |date= 2025-09-02 |access-date=2025-09-02 |website=Fenerbahce.org |language=tr}}</ref> On 14 September, he made his debut with the team in a 1–0 [[Süper Lig]] victory against [[Trabzonspor]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2025/9/fenerbahce-1-0-trabzonspor |title=Fenerbahçe 1-0 Trabzonspor |publisher=Fenerbahçe S.K. |language=tr |date=14 September 2025 }}</ref> On 24 September, he made his continental debut with the team in a [[UEFA Europa League]] match against [[GNK Dinamo Zagreb|Dinamo Zagreb]] which was resulted with a 3–1 away defeat.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2025/9/gnk-dinamo-zagreb-3-1-fenerbahce |title=GNK Dinamo Zagreb 3-1 Fenerbahçe |publisher=Fenerbahçe S.K. |language=tr |date=24 September 2025 }}</ref>

On 10 January 2026, he won a 2–0 victory against [[the Intercontinental Derby (football)|arch rival]] [[Galatasaray S.K. (football)|Galatasaray]] with his team in [[2025 Turkish Super Cup final]] played at [[Atatürk Olympic Stadium]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.turkiyetoday.com/sports/fenerbahce-claims-turkcell-super-cup-with-2-0-derby-victory-over-galatasaray-3212717 |title=Fenerbahce claims Turkcell Super Cup with 2-0 derby victory over Galatasaray |publisher=Türkiye Today |date=10 January 2026 }}</ref> It also marked his second trophy at the same stadium, coming nearly two and a half years after he won the [[2023 UEFA Champions League final]] with his former club Manchester City. A month later, on 23 February, due to injury sustained in the [[Süper Lig]] match against [[Kasımpaşa S.K.|Kasımpaşa]], he would be out for three weeks, as stated by coach [[Domenico Tedesco]] in the post-match press conference.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2026/2/teknik-direktorumuz-domenico-tedesco-dan-aciklamalar|title=Teknik Direktörümüz Domenico Tedesco'dan açıklamalar|date=23 February 2026|website=fenerbahce.org|language=tr}}</ref> Two months later, on 17 April, he conceded a stoppage-time equaliser in a 2–2 draw with [[Çaykur Rizespor]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ntvspor.net/foto-galeri/edersondan-caykur-rizespor-maci-sonrasi-olay-haber-geldi-gorusmeler-tikandi-421345/2 |title=Ederson'dan Çaykur Rizespor maçı sonrası olay haber geldi! Görüşmeler tıkandı |publisher=NTVSpor |language=tr |date=20 April 2026 }}</ref> before being sent off in a 3–0 away defeat to Galatasaray on 26 April, a result that effectively ended his club's hopes of winning the league title.<ref>{{cite web |last=Afroni |first=Donny |url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/video-ederson-punches-var-monitor-furious-outburst-ex-man-city-star-sent-off-fenerbahce-derby-loss-to-galatasaray/blta54a61c58d1768eb |title=VIDEO: Ederson punches VAR monitor in furious outburst after ex-Man City star sent off in Fenerbahce's derby loss to Galatasaray |publisher=Goal.com |date=27 April 2026 }}</ref>

==International career==
[[File:2019 Final da Copa América 2019 - Coutinho, Bobby Firmino, Casemiro e Ederson (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright|Ederson (in black) at the [[2019 Copa América final]]]]
Ederson was named in [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]]'s provisional squad for [[Copa América Centenario]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.goal.com/brasilglobaltour/en/news/5457/brasil-global-tour/2016/04/29/22949232/dunga-names-40-man-preliminary-copa-america-squad |title=Dunga names 40-man preliminary Copa America squad |website=Goal (website) |date=29 April 2016 |access-date=30 June 2016 |archive-date=1 May 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160501235733/http://www.goal.com/brasilglobaltour/en/news/5457/brasil-global-tour/2016/04/29/22949232/dunga-names-40-man-preliminary-copa-america-squad |url-status=live }}</ref> but was cut from the final squad due to injury.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.maisfutebol.iol.pt/benfica/internacional/brasil-ederson-falha-a-copa-america-por-lesao|title=Brasil: Ederson falha a Copa América por lesão|website=Maisfutebol|language=pt|date=31 May 2016|access-date=31 October 2018|archive-date=21 September 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200921033629/http://www.maisfutebol.iol.pt/benfica/internacional/brasil-ederson-falha-a-copa-america-por-lesao|url-status=live}}</ref> His debut for the national team came in a 3–0 win over [[Chile national football team|Chile]] in a [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|2018 World Cup qualifier]] on 10 October 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/soccer/report?gameId=431551|title=Gabriel Jesus, Paulinho help Brazil end Chile's World Cup hopes|publisher=ESPN|date=11 October 2017|access-date=31 October 2018|archive-date=29 July 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230729130704/https://www.espn.com/soccer/report?gameId=431551|url-status=live}}</ref> In May 2018, he was named in [[Tite (football manager)|Tite]]'s final [[Brazil national football team|23-man squad]] for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup|World Cup]] in Russia.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44116590|title=World Cup: Neymar named in Brazil's 23-man squad|website=BBC Sport|date=14 May 2018|access-date=31 October 2018|archive-date=5 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180805131748/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44116590|url-status=live}}</ref>  Ederson was included in Brazil's 23-man squad for the [[2019 Copa América]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.football-italia.net/138152/brazil-name-copa-america-squad |title=Brazil name Copa America squad |website=Football Italia |date=17 May 2019 |access-date=21 May 2019 |archive-date=6 November 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201106131142/https://www.football-italia.net/138152/brazil-name-copa-america-squad |url-status=live }}</ref>

In June 2021, he made his major tournament debut for Brazil, starting and keeping a clean sheet in a 4–0 group stage victory over [[Peru national football team|Peru]] at the [[2021 Copa América]] as Tite made five changes.<ref>{{cite web|date=18 June 2021|title=Brazil cruise past Peru with 4–0 Copa America win|url=https://www.reuters.com/lifestyle/sports/brazil-cruise-past-peru-with-4-0-copa-america-win-2021-06-18/|access-date=18 June 2021|website=Reuters|archive-date=27 June 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210627202736/https://www.reuters.com/lifestyle/sports/brazil-cruise-past-peru-with-4-0-copa-america-win-2021-06-18/|url-status=live}}</ref> In the quarter-finals against Chile, he was chosen at the expense of [[Alisson Becker]],<ref>{{cite news |last1=Savarese |first1=Mauricio |title=Ederson gets start over Alisson for Brazil's Copa QF match |url=https://apnews.com/article/premier-league-ederson-europe-brazil-international-soccer-65f6e71d5df0146b2e74d23df6a8cb32 |access-date=31 May 2024 |work=Associated Press News |date=1 July 2021 |archive-date=31 May 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240531130318/https://apnews.com/article/premier-league-ederson-europe-brazil-international-soccer-65f6e71d5df0146b2e74d23df6a8cb32 |url-status=live }}</ref> winning that match 1–0 as well as the semi-finals against Peru.<ref>{{cite news |title=Copa America 2021: Brazil beat Peru 1–0 thanks to Lucas Paqueta's first-half goal |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/57731776 |access-date=31 May 2024 |work=BBC Sport |date=6 July 2021 |archive-date=31 May 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240531130318/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/57731776 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 10 July, he started in his nation's 1–0 defeat to rivals [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]] in the [[2021 Copa América final|final]].<ref name="2021CAFinalGuardian">{{cite news |last=Graham |first=Bryan Armen |date=10 July 2021 |title=Argentina 1–0 Brazil: Copa América final – as it happened |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2021/jul/10/argentina-v-brazil-copa-america-final-live |work=[[The Guardian]] |accessdate=13 July 2021 |archive-date=7 November 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221107143523/https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2021/jul/10/argentina-v-brazil-copa-america-final-live |url-status=live }}</ref>

Ederson was named in the squad for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] in Qatar.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Cortegana |first1=Mario |title=Tite announces Brazil's official World Cup squad list... with nine forwards! |url=https://www.marca.com/en/world-cup/2022/11/07/63694ca2e2704e5d958b4575.html |access-date=31 May 2024 |work=Marca|location=Spain |date=7 November 2022 |archive-date=31 May 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240531130318/https://www.marca.com/en/world-cup/2022/11/07/63694ca2e2704e5d958b4575.html |url-status=live }}</ref> He played one game for the quarter-finalists, a 1–0 loss to [[Cameroon national football team|Cameroon]] in the final group game once his team had already advanced to the last 16.<ref>{{cite news |title=Cameroon stun Brazil – but crash out of World Cup |url=https://www.france24.com/en/sport/20221202-cameroon-stun-brazil-%E2%80%93-but-crash-out-of-world-cup |access-date=31 May 2024 |publisher=France 24 |date=2 December 2022 |archive-date=31 May 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240531130319/https://www.france24.com/en/sport/20221202-cameroon-stun-brazil-%E2%80%93-but-crash-out-of-world-cup |url-status=live }}</ref> He was initially called up by [[Dorival Júnior]] for the [[2024 Copa América]], but was replaced before the tournament by [[Rafael (footballer, born 1989)|Rafael]] after being unable to recover from a fractured eye socket.<ref>{{cite news |title=Brazil replace injured keeper Ederson in Copa America squad |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/story/_/id/40181300/brazil-replace-ederson-copa-america-squad |access-date=31 May 2024 |publisher=ESPN |date=19 May 2024 |archive-date=31 May 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240531132646/https://www.espn.co.uk/football/story/_/id/40181300/brazil-replace-ederson-copa-america-squad |url-status=live }}</ref>

==Style of play==
Ederson has been described as an agile, commanding, and physically imposing keeper,<ref name="profiled">{{cite web|url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/11679/10897209/who-is-benficas-ederson-moraes-man-city-transfer-target-profiled|title=Who is Ederson Moraes? Manchester City's new goalkeeper profiled|website=Sky Sports|last1=Wilkinson|first1=Jack|date=8 June 2017|access-date=17 January 2018|archive-date=17 January 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180117131823/http://www.skysports.com/football/news/11679/10897209/who-is-benficas-ederson-moraes-man-city-transfer-target-profiled|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="perfect fit">{{cite news|url=http://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/man-city-keeper-ederson-news-13848752|title=Man City goalkeeper Ederson proving 'the perfect fit' for Pep Guardiola|newspaper=Manchester Evening News|last1=Fay|first1=Richard|date=2 November 2017|access-date=17 January 2018|archive-date=17 January 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180117131522/http://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/man-city-keeper-ederson-news-13848752|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/blog/2017/sep/10/manchester-city-liverpool-pep-guardiola-jurgen-klopp-ederson|title=Ederson's bravery exposes Liverpool's flaws on Jürgen Klopp's day to forget|newspaper=The Guardian|last1=Ronay|first1=Barney|date=10 September 2017|access-date=17 January 2018|archive-date=4 July 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240704055847/https://www.theguardian.com/football/blog/2017/sep/10/manchester-city-liverpool-pep-guardiola-jurgen-klopp-ederson|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="A&E GK Brazil Strengths">{{cite web |url=http://www.espn.com/soccer/club/brazil/205/blog/post/3440627/alisson-ederson-make-goalkeeper-one-of-brazils-greatest-strengths |title=Alisson, Ederson make goalkeeper one of Brazil's greatest strengths |publisher=ESPN |last1=Vickery |first1=Tim |date=2 April 2018 |access-date=21 January 2019 |archive-date=21 January 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190121232601/http://www.espn.com/soccer/club/brazil/205/blog/post/3440627/alisson-ederson-make-goalkeeper-one-of-brazils-greatest-strengths |url-status=live }}</ref> who possesses both physical strength and good reflexes<ref name="perfect fit"/><ref name="Who is Ederson?">{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2017/05/29/ederson-benfica-star-man-city-could-make-worlds-expensive-goalkeeper/ |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220112/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2017/05/29/ederson-benfica-star-man-city-could-make-worlds-expensive-goalkeeper/ |archive-date=12 January 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live|title=Who is Ederson? The Benfica star Man City could make the world's most expensive goalkeeper|newspaper=The Daily Telegraph|last1=Bull|first1=J.J.|date=29 May 2017|access-date=17 January 2018}}{{cbignore}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.calciomercato.com/news/1993-la-serie-la-caccia-al-portiere-25047|title=1993 – La Serie: la caccia al portiere|trans-title=1993 – The Series: hunt for:ederson bagus dalam kontrol bola.the,goalkeeper|website=Calciomercato.com|language=it|last1=Tramacere|first1=Emanuele|date=16 May 2017|access-date=16 January 2018|archive-date=1 January 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180101110215/http://www.calciomercato.com/news/1993-la-serie-la-caccia-al-portiere-25047|url-status=live}}</ref> and shot-stopping abilities between the posts.<ref name="profiled"/><ref name="Who is Ederson?"/> However, he is mostly highly regarded for his distribution and skill with the ball at his feet than for his abilities as shot-stopper:<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/man-city-ederson-guardiola-transfer-24014101|title=Ederson must improve but Man City truth is as clear as|accessdate=26 May 2022|work=Manchester Evening News|date=20 May 2022|archive-date=27 May 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220527041146/https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/man-city-ederson-guardiola-transfer-24014101|url-status=live}}</ref> his control and confidence on the ball enables him to retain possession and quickly play the ball out from the back on the ground with his hands or either foot – even when put under pressure – or launch an attack with long kicks.<ref name="profiled"/><ref name="perfect fit"/><ref name="Who is Ederson?"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.foxsports.it/2017/05/29/calciomercato-manchester-city-piu-cinquanta-milioni-ederson-moraes/|title=Calciomercato, follia Manchester City: più di 50 mln per Ederson Moraes|trans-title=Transfer market, Manchester City folly: more than 50 million for Ederson Moraes|website=foxsports.it|language=it|last1=Bizzarri|first1=Francesco|date=29 May 2017|access-date=16 January 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171019004748/https://www.foxsports.it/2017/05/29/calciomercato-manchester-city-piu-cinquanta-milioni-ederson-moraes/|archive-date=19 October 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name="nuovo Julio Cesar">{{cite web|url=http://www.calciomercato.com/news/inter-ecco-ederson-il-nuovo-julio-cesar-378496|title=Inter: ecco Ederson, il nuovo Julio Cesar|trans-title=Inter: here is Ederson, the new Julio Cesar|website=calciomercato.com|language=it|last1=Serra|first1=Matteo|date=12 May 2016|access-date=16 January 2018|archive-date=19 October 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171019004019/http://www.calciomercato.com/news/inter-ecco-ederson-il-nuovo-julio-cesar-378496|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/11679/11002959/ederson-one-of-the-best-with-his-feet-shay-given-tells-premier-league-daily|title=Ederson 'one of the best with his feet', Shay Given tells Premier League Daily|website=Sky Sports|date=24 August 2017|access-date=16 January 2018|archive-date=16 January 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180116201757/http://www.skysports.com/football/news/11679/11002959/ederson-one-of-the-best-with-his-feet-shay-given-tells-premier-league-daily|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="Golden gloves">{{cite web|url=https://www.thescore.com/news/1387066|title=Golden gloves: Manchester City's decision to sign Ederson paying off|publisher=The Score|last1=Campo|first1=Carlo|date=30 September 2017|access-date=17 January 2018|archive-date=4 July 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240704055846/https://www.thescore.com/news/1387066|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/soccer/english-premier-league/23/blog/post/3300856/man-city-keeper-ederson-as-important-as-david-de-gea-is-for-man-united|title=Man City keeper Ederson as important as David De Gea is for Man United|publisher=ESPN|last1=Ogden|first1=Mark|date=8 December 2017|access-date=17 January 2018|archive-date=4 July 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240704060350/https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/37487853/man-city-keeper-ederson-important-david-de-gea-man-united|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thescore.com/liga/news/1289056-perfect-player-series-building-a-flawless-goalkeeper|title=Perfect player series: Building a flawless goalkeeper|publisher=The Score|last1=Nesci|first1=Gianluca|date=24 July 2017|access-date=17 January 2018|archive-date=25 February 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230225130557/https://www.thescore.com/liga/news/1289056-perfect-player-series-building-a-flawless-goalkeeper|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/premier-league/ederson-profile-manchester-city-pep-guardiola-goalkeepers-feature-vs-liverpool-united-a8291301.html|title=How Ederson redefined what is expected of a Goalkeeper|newspaper=The Independent|last=Brown|first=Luke|date=6 April 2018|access-date=6 April 2018|archive-date=8 April 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180408183201/https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/premier-league/ederson-profile-manchester-city-pep-guardiola-goalkeepers-feature-vs-liverpool-united-a8291301.html|url-status=live}}</ref> Although naturally left-footed,<ref name="A&E GK Brazil Strengths"/> he is capable of using either foot.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.independent.ie/world-news/and-finally/who-on-earth-is-manchester-city-target-ederson-moraes-35767550.html |title=Who on Earth is Manchester City target Ederson Moraes? |newspaper=Irish Independent |last1=McLean |first1=Max |date=29 May 2017 |access-date=21 January 2019 |archive-date=21 January 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190121233952/https://www.independent.ie/world-news/and-finally/who-on-earth-is-manchester-city-target-ederson-moraes-35767550.html |url-status=live }}</ref> Regarding his distribution, former Manchester City goalkeeper [[Shay Given]] described Ederson as "the best goalkeeper in the world with his feet" in 2018;<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2018/04/06/ederson-vs-david-de-gea-shay-given-compares-premier-leagues/ |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220112/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2018/04/06/ederson-vs-david-de-gea-shay-given-compares-premier-leagues/ |archive-date=12 January 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live |title=Ederson vs David De Gea: Shay Given compares the Premier League's two best goalkeepers |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |last1=Given |first1=Shay |date=6 April 2018 |access-date=21 January 2019 }}{{cbignore}}</ref> his range of passing has also led to him be described as a ''[[Playmaker#Playmaking in other positions|playmaker]]'' in the media.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2018/dec/07/ederson-ball-playing-midfielder-goalkeeper-manchester-city |title=Ederson leads way as a ball-playing Premier League midfielder in gloves |newspaper=The Guardian |last1=Wilson |first1=Jonathan |date=7 December 2018 |access-date=21 January 2019 |archive-date=1 July 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200701115508/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2018/dec/07/ederson-ball-playing-midfielder-goalkeeper-manchester-city |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/soccer/2017/10/18/the-brick-wall-ederson-solving-keeper-issues-at-man-city/106762812/ |title='The Brick Wall': Ederson solving keeper issues at Man City |website=USA Today |last1=Douglas |first1=Steve |last2=Savarese |first2=Mauricio |date=18 October 2017 |access-date=21 January 2019 |archive-date=21 January 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190121233005/https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/soccer/2017/10/18/the-brick-wall-ederson-solving-keeper-issues-at-man-city/106762812/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

Ederson is also very quick when rushing off his line,<ref name="Golden gloves" /> and often functions as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)#Sweeper-keeper|sweeper-keeper]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/soccer/english-premier-league/23/blog/post/3220404/manchester-citys-34-7-million-bet-on-ederson-is-paying-off|title=Manchester City's £34.7 million bet on Ederson is paying off|publisher=ESPN|last1=Smith|first1=Jonathan|date=4 October 2017|access-date=17 January 2018|archive-date=17 January 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180117132109/http://www.espn.com/soccer/english-premier-league/23/blog/post/3220404/manchester-citys-34-7-million-bet-on-ederson-is-paying-off|url-status=live}}</ref> Regarded as a highly promising prospect in his formative years,<ref name="Who is Ederson?" /> he stood out for his decision making, consistency, and composure in goal, as well as his ability to organise his defence, and has also become an intelligent reader of the game;<ref name="profiled" /><ref name="perfect fit" /><ref name="Who is Ederson?" /><ref name="nuovo Julio Cesar" /> in 2019, [[Kasper Schmeichel]] described him as the best goalkeeper in the Premier League.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11679/11710364/kasper-schmeichel-rates-ederson-as-the-best-goalkeeper-in-the-premier-league |title=Kasper Schmeichel rates Ederson as the best goalkeeper in the Premier League |website=Sky Sports |date=6 May 2019 |access-date=1 October 2019 |archive-date=1 October 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191001135941/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11679/11710364/kasper-schmeichel-rates-ederson-as-the-best-goalkeeper-in-the-premier-league |url-status=live }}</ref>

==Personal life==
Ederson acquired Portuguese citizenship in 2016.<ref>{{cite news|last=Rodrigues|first=Vítor|date=24 September 2016|title=Ederson e Jardel já são portugueses|trans-title=Ederson and Jardel are already Portuguese|url=https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/1a-liga/benfica/noticias/interior/ederson-e-jardel-ja-portugueses-5407055.html|language=pt|newspaper=O Jogo|access-date=16 March 2018|archive-date=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401194010/https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/1a-liga/benfica/noticias/interior/ederson-e-jardel-ja-portugueses-5407055.html|url-status=dead}}</ref> His body is heavily covered in tattoos, including a rose and a skull on his neck, angel wings on his back, a Portuguese League trophy on his leg, which he won for Benfica in 2016 and in 2017, and even a tattoo of 'I Belong to Jesus' which conveys his Christian faith.<ref>{{cite web |title=Man City's £35m Signing Ederson Is Covered In Amazing Tattoos |url=https://www.foottheball.com/players-in-focus/manchester-citys-35million-signing-ederson-covered-amazing-tattoos-including-flowers-faces-skulls-religious-icons/213698 |website=foottheball.com |date=2 June 2017 |access-date=25 October 2018 |archive-date=25 January 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220125145841/https://www.foottheball.com/players-in-focus/manchester-citys-35million-signing-ederson-covered-amazing-tattoos-including-flowers-faces-skulls-religious-icons/213698/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 10 May 2018, Ederson set a [[Guinness World Record]] for the longest football [[drop kick]], reaching a distance of 75.35 metres (247&nbsp;ft 2 in) at the [[Etihad Campus]].<ref name="guinness">{{cite news |url=https://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/news/2018/5/watch-man-citys-ederson-smash-drop-kick-title-as-yet-more-records-go-to-english |title=Watch Man City's Ederson smash drop kick title as yet more records go to English champions |date=20 May 2018 |access-date=9 May 2026 |newspaper=[[Guinness World Records]]}}</ref>

